# Export custom object definitions

Learn how to export custom object definitions in the Zuora UI.

1.  Navigate to in the left navigation.
2.  Select the checkboxes of the custom objects that you want to export.
3.  If you want to export the selected custom object definitions to a JSON file, click the Export to JSON icon ![Download icon](https://zuora.deploy.heretto.com/v4/deployments/QPAZk6lsgXwvotedNERE/object/24487eaa-f18e-45ce-9957-fa78d22712d4?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..y8plLU7PnNTGa9dmVzdG4A6vQseGa_JfbSvRwm8WV8w). If you want to copy the definitions to the clipboard, click the Copy to Clipboard icon ![Copy icon](https://zuora.deploy.heretto.com/v4/deployments/QPAZk6lsgXwvotedNERE/object/ed6f6dd9-9252-4592-9293-0add0417fa3d?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..nqdot1yMV3GMbvw_ViGxOLTL6m0p6q6143gGMpoFlzg). You can then import these selected custom object definitions to another tenant with the exported JSON file or from the clipboard.
